observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management: 

(a.)	Issue demand letter to notify the concerned officials and employees of their responsibility to settle their unliquidated cash advances and to employees who resigned/transferred to immediately cause the liquidation or settlement of the unliquidated cash advances;

(b.)	Stop the practice of granting additional cash advances to AO and personnel who still have unliquidated cash advances;

(c.)	The Municipal Treasurer to strictly monitor the submission of liquidation reports on time to ensure timely accounting thereof to avoid undue accumulation of outstanding cash advances; and,

(d.)	Take appropriate action for the full settlement of the year-end balance of cash advances.

