a) Payment of salaries of concerned officials/employees should not be paid unless cash advances are fully settled;

Demand letters should be issued to concerned officers/employees and    disciplinary actions should be imposed to those with long overdue accounts. In case of failure to settle their accountabilities, cause the withholding or suspensions of their salaries; and 

Stop the practice of granting additional cash advance when previous cash advances remained unliquidated/unsettled.

RECOMMENDATIONS:
We recommended that Management strictly observe the prescribing rules and regulations, and rates of expenses and allowances under Executive Order (EO) No. 77, otherwise such transactions will be subject to suspension or disallowance;
Stop the practice of allowing travel liquidations that are inconsistent with EO 77.

1.	Direct the Municipal Engineer to coordinate meetings with contractors to expedite and complete the aforementioned projects;

2.	Direct the Municipal Planning and Development Officer to conduct better preliminary detailed engineering to address right-of-way issues prior to project implementation, hence projects with right-of-way issues should not be implemented and funded until resolved;

3.	Issue work suspension/time extension orders for delays caused by right-of-way problems and bad weather;

4.	Direct the Project Engineers to strictly monitor and supervise the infrastructure projects implemented by this Municipality to prevent time lag and delays.

Strictly observe prudence on the use of government funds for meals and snacks by ensuring that these are utilized only for expenses which are regular and necessary;
Discontinue the provision of meals and snacks during meetings, celebrations and other activities, as these are embedded in the regular functions and responsibilities of the concerned officials and employees;
Stop the practice of disbursing for expenses for meals and snacks that do not actually exist as these constitute illegal expenditures and will be disallowed in audit;
Strictly observe the proper procedures and appropriate mode of procurement in the purchase of meals and snacks as prescribed in Republic Act No. 9184 and its Revised Implementing Rules; and
Attach to the disbursement vouchers for meals and snacks the required supporting documents duly accomplished as provided in Section 4.6 of Presidential Decree No. 1445.

We recommended that the Management initiate the following actions:

Discontinue the transferring of Funds from 20% DF to General Fund and adhere to the established rules and regulations in the utilization of 20% Development Fund;

Submit an explanation /justification to support the above stated Transfer of Funds.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the General Services Officer, BAC Secretariat and all the Department Heads to:

Formulate the Municipality's APP in accordance with Section 7 of the Revised IRR of RA No. 9184;

Ensure that all the necessary information required in the APP and its amendments are reflected therein for its continuous relevance and usefulness as a planning and control tool;

	Submit the duly approved copy of APP to the GPPB in accordance with Section 1(a) of Executive Order No. 662, series of 2007, as amended;

Attach the authenticated photo copy of the APP to the disbursement vouchers for the payment of all types of procurement, in compliance to COA Circular 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012; and

Include in the APP, provisions for foreseeable emergencies based on historical records as well as the manner of procurement thereof.

We recommended that Management:

Direct the Municipal Accountant to prepare Journal Entry Voucher (JEV) to correct the affected accounts in conformity with Section 04 	(p), Chapter 2 of the New Government Accounting system (NGAS) for LGUs; 

Strictly adhere to the provisions of the Section 79 of P.D 1445 on the 	disposal of the unserviceable properties;

Create Inventory Committee headed by the Municipal Treasurer to conduct actual physical inventory and sort out the unserviceable properties to be reported to IIRUP properly witnessed by the Auditor.

